OL,5, A group of green-minded Tory MPs says  
OL,6, the government should fund             
OL,7, environmental and social energy        
OL,8, policies from the Treasury, instead of 
OL,9, from consumer bills.                   
OL,11,FThe Conservative Environment Network   
OL,12,F(CEN) of 116 MPs says the temporary    
OL,13,Fmeasure would ease the surge in        
OL,14,Fhousehold costs.                       
OL,16,FBut the group opposes a separate       
OL,17,Fproposal to abolish the 5% VAT on      
OL,18,Fenergy bills, saying it would          
OL,19,Feffectively provide a subsidy for      
OL,20,Ffossil fuels.                          
